Package weka.classifiers.rules.vfdr

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Antd
    Antecedents (literals) make up rules.
    AttributeStats
    Stores the sufficient statistics about an attribute for a given rule.
    CandidateAntd
    Class holding a antecedent that is candidate for rule expansion.
    ClassificationStrategy
    Classification strategies applying to a ruleset.
    ClassificationStrategy.FirstHit
    Classification strategy for ordered sets.
    ClassificationStrategy.WeightedMax
    Classification strategy for unordered rule sets.
    ExpansionMetric
    Metrics evaluate the merit of an expansion (given the pre and post expansion class distribution) to chose the best.
    ExpansionMetric.Entropy
    Actually this metric is information gain.
    GaussianAttributeStats
    Attribute stats for numeric attributes.
    NominalAntd
    Nominal antecedent, of the form {NominalAttribute = value}.
    NominalAttributeStats
    Attribute stats for nominal attributes.
    NumericAntd
    Antecedent for numerical attributes, of the form {NumericAttribute <= number} or {NumericAttribute > number}.
    SufficientStats
    Sufficient statistics used to grow rules and make predictions on unlabeled instances.
    SufficientStats.MajorityClass
    Implements the majority class strategy to classify an instance.
    SufficientStats.NaiveBayes
    Sufficient stats for a rule that uses a naive Bayes strategy to classify instances.
    VfdrRule
    Represents a rule for the Vfdr algorithm.
